From: Opsero <noreply@opsero.com>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm: xlnx: drv: disable vblank before cleanup on shutdown

After the v_mix DRM bridge pipeline is in use, `sudo poweroff` /
`reboot` triggers this WARN_ON in the drm_managed cleanup path:

    xlnx-mixer ...: drm_WARN_ON(vblank->enabled &&
                                drm_core_check_feature(dev, DRIVER_MODESET))
    WARNING at drivers/gpu/drm/drm_vblank.c:507 drm_vblank_init_release
    Call trace:
      drm_vblank_init_release
      drm_managed_release
      drm_dev_put
      xlnx_unbind

The CRTC's vblank counter is still in the "enabled" state when the
drm_managed cleanup runs because xlnx_unbind goes straight to
drm_dev_unregister + drm_dev_put without first asking the modeset stack
to power outputs down.

The canonical fix is drm_atomic_helper_shutdown(), which walks every
CRTC and commits an atomic transition to "DPMS off" — disabling
encoders, planes and vblank along the way. Call it at the start of
xlnx_unbind so subsequent drm_managed cleanup has nothing left to
complain about. The system still powers off correctly without this
(the WARN is non-fatal), but the trace shows up in `dmesg` on every
shutdown which is noisy.

Signed-off-by: Opsero <noreply@opsero.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c
@@ -283,6 +283,7 @@ static void xlnx_unbind(struct device *dev)
 	struct xlnx_drm *xlnx_drm = dev_get_drvdata(dev);
 	struct drm_device *drm = xlnx_drm->drm;

+	drm_atomic_helper_shutdown(drm);
 	drm_dev_unregister(drm);
 	component_unbind_all(&xlnx_drm->master->dev, drm);
 	if (xlnx_drm->fb) {
--
2.34.1
